The paper deals with question answering, which is a natural language processing task, and proposes a novel training framework that utilizes unlabeled text to improve performance. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper involves training a generative model and developing domain adaptation algorithms, which are techniques commonly used in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with information retrieval, which is a sub-field of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses reinforcement learning, which is a technique commonly used in the sub-category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
